limerick_list.text:
A bout is a battle of quickness;
A contest, in sumo, of thickness;
A binge, if you're boozing;
A cold, if you're losing
A battle to keep away sickness.

Watch my front, watch my sides, watch my back;
I'm afraid of a lethal attack.
Excubation is hard;
We are always on guard.
I can't even go out for a snack.

Shooting trophies comes easy, indeed;
Lazy hunters get all that they need.
Countless killings await;
Daily bags will be great.
At the game ranch, it's all guaranteed.

My messy behaviour must stop;
There are stains where I've let coffee slop;
All my tools out of place,
Ribbons tangle with lace:
My craft room's all over the shop.

I can't think of anything nicer
Than hummus that's made from the cicer;
For a meal it is hip,
Or a dip with a chip;
This chickpea's a potent enticer.

It paints colourful arcs in the sky;
Launched the arrow that pierced a king's eye;
When it's drawn across strings,
How the melody sings;
When you fumble your bow, it's a tie.

Yellow's five; three's light green; red is two;
Purple's four; white is one; nine is blue;
Eight is brown; seven's black;
Dark green's six. Got the knack?
Orange ten. Count again. This I knew.

The Bikini would warn of attack:
No concerns when at white or at black;
At black special, take care;
If at amber, beware;
If at red, run away!  Don't look back!
